ful because:\n\n* It wouldn't work for 0×0 matrices.\n* More things are true about diagonal matrices than constant matrices, and so more lemmas exist.\n\n`Matrix.diagonal_unique` can be used to reach this form, while `Ring.inverse_eq_inv` can be used\nto replace `Ring.inverse` with `⁻¹`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/NonsingularInverse.html#Matrix.inv_subsingleton","kind":"theorem","line":584,"name":"Matrix.inv_subsingleton","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/NonsingularInverse.lean#L584-L600"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/NonsingularInverse.html#Matrix.inv_diagonal\"><span class=\"name\">Matrix</span>.<span class=\"name\">inv_diagonal</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u'}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Defs.html#Fintype\">Fintype</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidableEq\">DecidableEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span cl